StringWithMarkup.String: In some commercially available injections, the air has been replaced with nitrogen to avoid oxidation. Withdrawal of doses from multiple-dose vials introduces air into the vials, subjecting the remaining epinephrine to oxidation. Oxidation of the drug imparts first a pink, then a brown color; epinephrine preparations must not be used if they have a pinkish or darker than slightly yellow color or contain a precipitate.

Reference: American Society of Health System Pharmacists; AHFS Drug Information 2009. Bethesda, MD. (2009), p. 1394
